 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above.JOHANNESBURG - DA leader, Mmusi Maimane is convinced the ANC's factional war is beyond the party's control.Maimane referred to two warring factions who have now turned to the courts in KwaZulu-Natal to intercede.Maimane was addressing the Cape Town Press Club on Thursday about the failure of the motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma."I welcome the results of last week s vote, because in many ways it unprecedented...it demonstrated there s a profound disunity in the ANC... It's at war with itself..I think this is worth reflecting on," said Maimane. Last week, the DA was vocal in a calling for early elections as one of the possible steps to remove Zuma from power. READ: ANC: three MPs to be disciplined over no confidence voteZuma survived the vote, but by a narrower margin than on seven previous occasions.eNCA